Buat yang tertarik untuk belajar surfing, tapi masih pemula banget dan hanya berniat untuk sekadar pengen tau aja, Pantai Kuta adalah tempat yang pas buat kamu.
Di sini disewakan papan seluncur dan bahkan ada instrukturnya yang mengajari dasarnya. Pantainya dangkal dan tidak berbatu jadi aman banget. Ada bonus pemandangan sunset yang bagus banget juga!
--
For those of you who'd like to learn surfing but doesn't have the basic and only trying to be the casual surfer, Kuta Beach is the place for you. It offers surf boards to be rented and there are instructors that will teach you the basics. The beach is also shallow and doesn't have too many rocks. And that sunset view tho! Stunning!

Simwonsa Temple, South Korea

This is a traditional market located around Jongno-gu Area in Seoul, South Korea.

Batam Cable Ski Park ( BCP ). This location already exists for more than ten years in Batam, Indonesia. It's a place for wakeboarding, which is a water sport where you ride a wakeboard and surf on the surface of water. But here you are pulled by some mechanical tool instead of actual Boat.

For Rp 350.000 ( ~ 25 USD ) you can play for a day. There are a lot of trainers and skilled customers who will gladly help you about the wakeboarding technique.

caption.text:
Tangkuban Perahu, Bandung.
A beautiful dormant volcano in West Java, Indonesia.

The view is amazing but the smell might be a little bit weird due to the large amount of sulphur around.
You have to come in the right time ( usually midday ) to get a clear view because normally there are clouds that will block your sight.
